value.value: Skeletal element that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial element.
Skeletal element of the branchial arches located medial to the epibranchials.
Most anterior pharyngobranchial element, located medial to the epibranchials.
Pharyngobranchial element, located medial to the epibranchials and posteriorly adjacent to pharyngobranchial 1 element.
Pharyngobranchial element, located medial to the epibranchials and posteriorly adjacent to pharyngobranchial 2 element.
Most posterior pharyngobranchial element, located medial to the epibranchials.
Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 1.
Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 2.
Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 3.
Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 4.
Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 5.
Anatomical structure that is formed as a hiatus in the muscles covering the anterior chamber of the swim bladder in the area of ribs 5 and 6.
Surface structure that is a fleshy membrane covering part of the eye.
Joint between the left and right frontal bone.
Canal that houses the dorsal aorta.
Foramina that allow passage of occipital arteries.
Foramen for passage of nerve supplying otic lateral line.
Fossa or chamber on posterior portion of orbital region of neurocranium that serves as attachment site for posterior extrinsic eye muscles.
Fossa or chamber on anterior portion of orbital region of neurocranium that serves as attachment site for anterior extrinsic eye musculature.
Fossa of opercle that articulates with hyomandibular condyle for opercle.
Process of the epioccipital that extends posteriorly, is laminar in form and is usually attached to Weberian apparatus.
Dermal bone that is located lateral to vomer off midline of palate. Accessory vomerine tooth plate bears teeth and may be present as one or more pairs.

definition.value: Accessory vomerine tooth plate is not synonymous with dermopalatine tooth plate, palatine tooth plate, or pterygoid tooth plate.

value.value: Scute that is an elongated plate associated with a ligament running between posterior nuchal plate and rib on vertebra 6. Infranuchal scute is paired and develops from its associated ligament and sensory canal tubular ossicle.
Dermal bone that is ring-shaped or cylindrical and surrounds a sensory canal.
Sensory canal that is a side branch between a sensory canal proximally and a pore at its distal end. Sensory canal tubule is bilaterally paired although often imperfectly so.
Dermal bone that is located on midline of snout in skin above mesethmoid and lateral ethmoid bones. Rostral plate bears type 1 odontodes and is unpaired.
Lip that is expanded to form a broad, rounded cup around the mouth.
Barbel that is attached to the anterior rim of the posterior nostril. Posterior nasal barbel is paired.
Barbel that is associated with the anterior nostril. Anterior nasal barbel is paired.
Barbel that is attached to the distal end of the maxilla and that originates on the side of the mouth. Maxillary barbel is paired.
Joint that articulates the left and right basipterygium cartilage or bone. Inter-basipterygium joint is unpaired.
Joint between the centra, and sometimes the neural arches or parapophyses of vertebra 4 and vertebra 5.
Joint that articulates the orbitosphenoid cartilage or bone and lateral ethmoid cartilage or bone. Orbitosphenoid-lateral ethmoid joint is paired.
Joint that articulates the autopalatine cartilage or bone and maxilla.
Ligament that connects the metapterygoid to the autopalatine.
Lateral ethmoid-autopalatine ligament is a ligament that connects the lateral ethmoid to the autopalatine.
Mesethmoid-premaxillary ligament is a ligament that connects the mesethmoid to the premaxilla.
Mesethmoid-maxillary ligament is a ligament that connects the mesethmoid to the maxilla.
Joint that articulates the hyomandibular cartilage or bone and otic region cartilage or sphenotic bone, and often pterotic bone and prootic bone. Hyomandibular-otic region joint is paired.
Process that is part of the anal fin lepidotrichium.
Process that is part of the caudal fin lepidotrichium.

definition.value: Caudal fin hook is found in some characiform fishes.

value.value: Joint that articulates the left and right premaxillary bones. Inter-premaxillary joint is unpaired.
Surface structure that is a portion of skin that projects or hangs from the body.
Tooth row that is on the dentary.
